A vintage 1950s advertisement-style illustration of a retro desktop computer with an absurdly complex array of spinning dials, blinking vacuum tubes, and tangled wires erupting from its beige cabinet. The machine sits on a mid-century modern desk with chrome legs, surrounded by scattered coffee cups and crumpled papers. Steam comically rises from the overheating device while a small desk fan attempts to cool it. The color palette features warm yellows, oranges, and turquoise typical of 1950s commercial art, with halftone dot patterns and slightly faded edges giving it an aged magazine quality.
